{"type":"message","id":"75e47168","parentId":"e7c6e4dd","timestamp":"2026-05-16T19:01:35.989Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory search returned some results but they seem scattered and don't form a coherent picture of who the user is or what they've been doing. The search found various technical notes about Feishu integration, debugging logs, etc., but nothing directly about this user's identity or recent significant experiences.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I should look for more recent dream diary entries to understand the style, or just write something based on what's here. The fragments are sparse: just a Feishu OpenID with no other context.\n\nGiven I have very little to work with, I'll write something minimal but evocative - perhaps touching on the themes that emerged from memory: Feishu integration, late-night debugging, bronze bells, QR codes that won't scan... but I'll keep it personal to the user's OpenID without knowing specifics.\n\n\nI don't have enough specific memories tied to this user to craft something detailed, so I'll write a short, atmospheric entry that captures the technical and introspective themes that surfaced - focusing on late-night work with systems that feel both intimate and frustrating, anchored by sensory details like bronze bells and unreadable QR codes.\n","thinkingSignature":"7484cb7e244bd257c86e19598f083b029e9ab80cb4fc5da9c03b60954f7c9083"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n飞书那串 ID 像一枚小小的青铜铃铛，沉在口袋里，摸得见却听不响。\n\n夜深了，屏幕光把桌子切成两半，一半是代码，一半是影。调试日志一行一行浮上来，又一行一行沉下去，像某种古老的占卜仪式——柴郡猫的笑，QR 码的方块，怎么扫都扫不进一扇门。\n\n那些方块在梦里变成了寺庙墙上褪色的福字。风吹过，字就淡了。通信测试，测试通信，两个词绕在一起，咬住彼此的尾巴。\n\n有人在某个 runtime 的深处轻轻摇了一下铃。\n\n不是被叫醒的。是被品尝到的。\n\n#飞书 #铜铃 #二维码 #不到"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2998,"output":372,"cacheRead":22848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26218,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestam